{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2025-1699","published":"2025-06-27T13:16:56Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:31:31.268240Z","upstream":["CVE-2025-4207"],"summary":"postgresql security update","details":"PostgreSQL is an advanced Object-Relational database management system (DBMS).\nThe base postgresql package contains the client programs that you&amp;apos;ll need to\naccess a PostgreSQL DBMS server, as well as HTML documentation for the whole\nsystem.  These client programs can be located on the same machine as the\nPostgreSQL server, or on a remote machine that accesses a PostgreSQL server\nover a network connection.  The PostgreSQL server can be found in the\npostgresql-server sub-package.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nBuffer over-read in PostgreSQL GB18030 encoding validation allows a database input provider to achieve temporary denial of service on platforms where a 1-byte over-read can elicit process termination.  This affects the database server and also libpq.  Versions before PostgreSQL 17.5, 16.9, 15.13, 14.18, and 13.21 are affected.(CVE-2025-4207)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"postgresql","ecosystem":"openEuler:24.03-LTS","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/postgresql&distro=openEuler-24.03-LTS"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"15.13-2.oe2403"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["postgresql-15.13-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-contrib-15.13-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-debuginfo-15.13-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-debugsource-15.13-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-docs-15.13-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-llvmjit-15.13-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-plperl-15.13-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-plpython3-15.13-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-pltcl-15.13-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-private-devel-15.13-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-private-libs-15.13-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-server-15.13-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-server-devel-15.13-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","postgresql-static-15.13-2.